Tablet Manufacturing Process at WeloxPharma

At WeloxPharma, tablet manufacturing is a highly controlled and precise process, designed to ensure each dose delivers safety, consistency, and therapeutic effectiveness. Tablets are solid, oral dosage forms typically consumed with water and are one of the most widely used methods of medication delivery.

The process begins with the careful blending of active pharmaceutical ingredients (APIs) with suitable excipients — substances that help with binding, stability, and absorption. This powdered blend is then compressed using advanced machinery to form compact tablets of uniform size and strength.

Once formed, the tablets undergo rigorous quality checks to verify their hardness, disintegration time, and chemical integrity. This guarantees that each tablet activates at the right time inside the digestive system for optimal effect.

WeloxPharma ensures that the entire production process aligns with Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) and complies with both national and international pharmaceutical standards. Our commitment to excellence enables us to manufacture tablets that are not only safe and effective but also ready for global distribution.

Step-by-Step Process:

  1. Accurate Weighing & Blending

The first critical step in our tablet production process involves the precise weighing of both active pharmaceutical ingredients (APIs) and excipients. These substances are then blended in a controlled environment to achieve a uniform distribution, which is essential for consistency in every tablet.

  1. Granulation – Building the Perfect Base

Once the components are uniformly blended, the next stage is granulation. This process transforms the powder mixture into granules, enhancing the flow and compressibility of the formulation. Our expert team follows strict formulation guidelines to ensure each batch maintains potency and stability.

  1. Compression – Shaping with Precision

The granulated mix is carefully sieved to eliminate impurities. After thorough quality checks, it is compressed into solid tablets using high-speed machines. At WeloxPharma, our compression units operate under the supervision of skilled professionals who ensure each tablet meets the desired hardness, weight, and integrity.

  1. Coating – For Functionality and Appearance

Our tablets go through a coating process using advanced equipment that ensures uniformity in color, texture, and size. WeloxPharma facilities are equipped with fully automated, HVAC-controlled systems that maintain optimal hygiene and temperature for superior coating application.

  1. Rigorous Quality Control

Every batch of tablets is subjected to a comprehensive quality control protocol. From raw materials to the final product, our QA team performs stringent tests to ensure compliance with pharmacopoeial standards.
